                            <comment id="277832" author="qian_wc" created="Fri, 21 Aug 2020 03:16:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The following is Siyao&apos;s comment about the patch:&lt;br/&gt;
Implementing mkdir() by using intent lock is basically wrong: mkdir is a reint operation, if it is done in the way using intent lock, it can not guarantee recovery works. If using intent lock, during recovery it will just replay the lock, will not replay to re-execute the mkdir request...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hi Andreas,&lt;br/&gt;
Could you please comment on it?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Qian&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
